About
=====

  The example programs in the current directory use libprimesieve to
  generate, count and print primes and prime k-tuplets.

  The example programs are documented in doc/USAGE_EXAMPLES.
  doc/LIBPRIMESIEVE explains how to build libprimesieve in more
  detail.

How to compile the example programs
===================================

  Open a terminal or 'Visual Studio Command Prompt' and cd into the
  primesieve directory. The following commands build and install
  libprimesieve and compile the example programs.

  For Unix-like OSes (Linux, Mac OS X, ...) and GNU g++
  -----------------------------------------------------

  $ make lib
  $ sudo make install
  $ make examples

  For Windows and Microsoft Visual C++
  ------------------------------------

  > nmake -f Makefile.msvc lib
  > nmake -f Makefile.msvc dist
  > nmake -f Makefile.msvc examples

  For MinGW (with MSYS) and Cygwin with GNU g++
  ---------------------------------------------

  $ make lib
  $ make install
  $ make examples

Other C++ compilers (e.g. clang++)
==================================

  $ make lib CXX=clang++
  $ sudo make install
  $ make examples CXX=clang++

  If your compiler supports OpenMP 3.0 or later you can add the
  corresponding flag e.g. CXXFLAGS="-O2 -openmp" to both the lib and
  examples targets.
